[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Printing a 3D figure with individual parts from&nbsp; a 2D image is now easier and faster with the help&nbsp;&nbsp; of AI than ever before. I\'m going to show you the&nbsp; whole workflow from first creating our reference&nbsp;&nbsp; image, then generating the 3D model, splitting&nbsp; it into different parts with actual connectors,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'and taking it then into your 3D slicer, all inside&nbsp; only one tool and in only a few minutes. So,&nbsp;&nbsp; let\'s get started. Hey guys, and welcome back&nbsp; to the channel. My name is Philip from Pixel&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Artistry. So before we jump in, why do we even&nbsp; use AI for 3D printing in the first place? Because&nbsp;&nbsp; normally you would either need like real skyping&nbsp; skills like in ZBrush for example or Blender or&nbsp;&nbsp; you would spend hours cutting the model in parts&nbsp; by hand. And this is obviously a lot of work and&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'takes a lot of time and AI can definitely speed&nbsp; up that process. And this is what I\'m also going&nbsp;&nbsp; to show you today with High 3D actually. And great&nbsp; thing is as well that it\'s way easier than before&nbsp;&nbsp; because I am myself still a complete beginner when&nbsp; it comes to 3D printing and even for me the whole&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'workflow was no problem at all and it was actually&nbsp; quite fun to have than the end results in my hand&nbsp;&nbsp; with the printed 3D figure. They made it really&nbsp; easy to go from a 2D image to a printed 3D model. So first thing is actually that we get started&nbsp; with the image generation. And I\'m here at the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'highd.ai AI homepage. Once you\'re here, you can&nbsp; see in the image section that here we can then&nbsp;&nbsp; enter prompt to directly create your reference&nbsp; image. And this is of course really great because&nbsp;&nbsp; you don\'t need to jump around any tools anymore&nbsp; and you can directly generate the image here&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'then take it into 3D and then print it afterwards.&nbsp; And let\'s start with it. So basically I\'m putting&nbsp;&nbsp; in here a prompt and basically the keywords in my&nbsp; prompts are always that I\'m using like full body.&nbsp;&nbsp; Then of course I describe what kind of character&nbsp; I would like to have. In this case here fighter.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'I would also have here like this 3D model look&nbsp; and a solid background. So it\'s much easier to&nbsp;&nbsp; separate it from the background. And once we have&nbsp; that, you can then also choose here your AR model.&nbsp;&nbsp; Most of the times I\'m using here Nano Banana 2&nbsp; or Nano Banana Pro. Once you have this selected,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'then just make sure that you choose your size&nbsp; here. For this one, I always go with one by one&nbsp;&nbsp; because it makes the most sense when we create&nbsp; a character. Then you can also choose the image&nbsp;&nbsp; ratio here, how many you would like to generate.&nbsp; I\'m taking here four most of the times just to&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'have variations with one prompt. You can also&nbsp; choose your multiv- view by the way where you&nbsp;&nbsp; can then generate your model from each angle. You&nbsp; could also even upload your image reference in&nbsp;&nbsp; case you have something really specific in mind&nbsp; and could go from there. But once we have that,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'basically we\'re ready to go and I can hit here&nbsp; generate. And then once generated, you can see&nbsp;&nbsp; that the generator gives us four different&nbsp; images. So basically you could go with one of&nbsp;&nbsp; those options or you could regenerate and then of&nbsp; course look for a better result. I ended up then&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'with a character like this one here where I really&nbsp; like the style of her. So the great thing is once&nbsp;&nbsp; you\'re then happy you can then directly go here&nbsp; to image to 3D because here I can recommend highly&nbsp;&nbsp; to use the version 2.1 here. You can then also&nbsp; choose the model type. So you can choose between&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'fast and quality. Most of the times I\'m using&nbsp; here the quality one. Then you can use here also&nbsp;&nbsp; geometry or texture. For printing I usually only&nbsp; need the geometry type. So I\'m choosing this one.&nbsp;&nbsp; And then you can also choose your license type.&nbsp; And you could even go to advanced settings even&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:13] [scene:talk]
